Kyu BJP ko 2024 Lok Sabha chunav mein vote nahi dena chahiye:

1. **Pradarshan**: Vishleshan karein ki BJP ne pichle samay mein kya pradarshan diya hai, desh ke star par aur aapke rajya ya nirvachan kshetra mein. Dekhein ki unhone apne vaade poore kiye hain aur kya ve mukhya mudde prabhavi tareeke se samjhe hain.

2. **Netaon ka Profile**: BJP ke pratinidhiyon ka profile jaanch lein jo aapke nirvachan kshetra mein hain. Unke pichhle anubhav, yogyata aur karya kaal ko moolyaankan karein, taki aap unki bhoomika ke liye samarpan de sakein.

3. **Gathbandhan**: Sochein ki BJP ne kisi doosri party ke saath koi gathbandhan ya sahyog banaya hai jo unke nitiyon aur nirnayon par prabhav dal sakta hai.

4. **Sankalp Patra**: BJP ki 2024 chunav ke liye Sankalp Patra ko padhein. Samjhein unke sujhav, yojnaen aur desh ke liye drishti ke saath ki ve aapke vicharon aur prathamiktaon se kitna mel khaate hain.

5. **Sthaniya Mudde**: Sochein ki BJP kaise sthaniya muddon ka samadhan karne ka iraada rakhti hai jo aapke liye aur aapke samudaay ke liye mahatvapurn hain. Dekhein kisi vishesh pahal ya yojna ko jo aapke kshetra ko labhanvit kar sakti hai.

6. **Netritva**: BJP ke netritva ko moolyaankan karein, sarkar chalane ki yogyata, party ko ek karne ki kshamata aur desh ko prabhavshali tareeke se netritva karne ki kshamata ko samjhein.

7. **Pratipaksha**: Vishwasniya srot, samudaay ke neta aur visheshagyaon se pratipaksha prapt karein, takki BJP aur unke sarkar par unke prabhav par vibhinn drishtikon prapt kar sakein.

I casted my vote in the urdu school of shantinagar constituency, bangalore around 4 pm. Here's what happened. The lady next to voting booth, said to me "Just cast for somebody and leave" To which I replied saying" It cannot be done like that and I will have a proper look of the candidates and then cast my vote." To which she sarcastically said "ok ok, you have 2 hrs to do, take your time".  And kept cribbing saying she is there since morning doing the same job.  So when I pressed the button, there was no beep or light glow nor did vvpad work. When I told her that, she initially said its like that but it's taken my vote, when I insisted, then pressed a button by her side, and then the beep sound came, but still there was no vvpad. I was startled at that kind of carelessness and cheeky behaviour of people there.  It was never like this before. I am casting vote for more than 20 yrs here. We had 1 or 2 people from our area in the polling station and they wld be so helpful in guiding people.  The most important work is given to such hooligans, incompetent people. What kind of fair voting are we expecting with such crippled system and such unethical/unrighteous people given the work at voting booths.

тЧП Vijay Ghorpade, Economist

During the Lok Sabha election period, the government had taken тВ╣1.65 lakh crore from the RBI, and now the RBI's reserves have come down to тВ╣30,000 crore. This indicates that not only the banks but also the RBI is on the path to insolvency... Isn't this an alarming bell?*

Why and how did this happen? The common citizen is not going to ask such questions today because they are engrossed in religious scriptures rather than economics. They may not even know that before 2014, no government had ever taken the entire 'surplus money - total profit' from the RBI. Only a portion was taken as a dividend by the government. In 2018, when Urjit Patel was the Governor of the RBI, the Modi government demanded all the profit money from the bank. However, Patel refused according to the rules, which led to his resignation from the governorship. Then the government established a 6-member committee under the chairmanship of former RBI Governor Bimal Jalan, which paved the way for the government. Until then, the maximum amount taken from the RBI as a dividend was тВ╣50/55 thousand crore. During the Bangladesh Liberation War, the then Prime Minister Mrs. Gandhi had asked the RBI for тВ╣70 thousand crore instead of тВ╣50 thousand crore, but the bank clearly refused, and the government accepted it. This government has not only changed the rules of the RBI for itself but also changed 323 to 27 laws for corporates and companies, whitewashing their deeds. In the last 3 to 5 years, 50 thousand companies went bankrupt. The banks' loans sank, and 70 thousand new companies stood up with new loans! This is the economics of this government!

Today, if the RBI does not have the expected тВ╣74 thousand crore profit and whatever little there is, is taken by the government, then who will save the sinking banks? You must remember banks like Lakshmi Vilas; Yes Bank; DHFL! Lakshmi Vilas was sold to a Singapore bank. The condition of the other two banks is still very bad, and now two more banks are being privatized. Instead of understanding whether Qutub Minar is 'Vishnu Stambha' or whether there is a 'Shivling' in Gyanvapi, we should understand where this economic policy of the government has brought the country.

The constitutional rule says that if inflation continues to rise for four consecutive months, the government should directly question the RBI! And the RBI should also give a proper response. But for the past 6 months, even though the inflation index has been rising, the government has neither questioned nor has the RBI provided any clarification. There should have been a discussion in the Parliament, but this government did not do so. Today's RBI board is appointed by the government, so who will be held accountable? Action against Urjit Patel was taken because he went against the government! With such glaring examples in front, who will go against the government? On the contrary, the government-appointed board has brought the RBI to this state by supporting the government.

Comparing the eight-year period of former Prime Minister Dr. Manmohan Singh from 2006 to 2014 with that of Modi from 2014 to 2022, it becomes evident that during Dr. Singh's tenure, the government took only тВ╣1,01,679 crore from the RBI, whereas during Modi's tenure, the amount is тВ╣5,74,976 crore! That's five times more! This is called 'corruption done cunningly through the system!' You decide who has really brought the RBI to insolvency!

Derogatory remarks by political leaders like Narendra Modi can have a significant negative impact on the social fabric and unity of a diverse country like India in several ways:

1. Divisiveness: When a leader uses derogatory language against a particular community, it can create divisions and animosity among different religious and ethnic groups. This can lead to tension, conflict, and a breakdown of social cohesion.

2. Marginalization: Derogatory remarks can contribute to the marginalization and alienation of the targeted community. It can make individuals feel excluded and discriminated against, leading to a sense of injustice and inequality.

3. Polarization: Such remarks can polarize society, leading to the formation of "us versus them" mentalities. This can further exacerbate existing social and religious tensions, making it difficult to foster understanding and cooperation among diverse groups.

4. Undermining Trust: Derogatory remarks by political leaders can undermine trust and confidence in the government and its ability to represent and protect the interests of all citizens. It can erode the trust between different communities and the government, leading to a breakdown in social harmony.

5. Impact on International Relations: Derogatory remarks can also have implications for India's international standing, affecting its relations with other countries and global organizations. It can tarnish the country's image as a diverse and inclusive society, impacting its diplomatic and economic ties.

Overall, derogatory remarks by political leaders have the potential to weaken the social fabric and unity of a diverse country like India, and it is essential for leaders to exercise restraint and promote inclusive, respectful discourse to foster a harmonious society.

*Upma was served in a breakfast every morning in a hostel with a capacity of 100 people.  Out of those 100 people, 80 people used to complain every day that different items should be made instead of upma.*
*But, the other 20 people were happy to eat upma.  The remaining 80 people wanted to cook something other than upma.*

*The hostel warden voting method was proposed as some decision had to be reached in this chaotic situation. 

 According to this, whichever tiffin gets the most votes, that tiffin will be cooked that day.*

 *20 students who wanted Upma cast their vote accurately.  The remaining 80 people cast their vote as follows.*
 18 - Masala Dosa
 16 - Aloo Parotta & Dahi
 14 - Roti & Subg
 12 - Bread & Butter
 10 - Noodles
 10 - Idli Sambar

 So, as per the voting results, Upma gets the highest number of votes, and again the same is served every day.

*Lesson:* As long as 80% of the population is selfish, divided and scattered, 20% will rule us.

 18 - Masala Dosa

 10 - Idli Sambar

*Lesson:* As long as 80% of the population is selfish, divided and scattered, 20% will rule us.

*This is a silent message.*

Dear Dhruv rathee,

I hope this  finds you well .My name is Biswas Kumar Singh I am reaching out to you on behalf of 27  lakhs people of Assam. As we have been facing a serious issue  from the last five years and there is no solution yet .We have  been following your work  and we believe that if you make a video on this topic every Indian will know about this and it will help us to get over this problem. Let me brief about the problem we are facing.

The All India United Democratic Front (AIUDF) on February 7 sought an end to the ordeal of more than 26.57 lakh people who have been unable to acquire Aadhaar cards after their biometrics were frozen during the exercise to update the National Register of Citizens (NRC) in Assam.

A total of 26,57,784 people were rejected in two NRC drafts published on December 31, 2017, and July 30, 2018, for failing to produce documentsthat could have established their citizenship.

Some 7.51 lakh of them were included in the complete draft published on August 31, 2019, following the claims and objections phase of the NRC. However, their biometrics along with those of the 19.06 lakh who could not make it to the citizenship list continued to remain frozen.

In 2022, Shajahan Ali Ahmad, a resident of Bongaigaon, Assam, faced an abrupt termination from his assistant manager position at a private bank due to his inability to maintain an Employees' Provident Fund (EPF) account.Ahmad is among the 27 lakh people who had submitted their biometric details with the government of Assam during the 'Claims and Objections' process in 2018.

Jeherin Nesha, a resident of Margherita, Assam, is a fellowship holder under Ministry of Minority Affairs and is also currently pursuing her PhD. She was awarded the Maulana Azad National Fellowship for Minority Students in April 2022, but it was unexpectedly halted in September of that year. This happened because she couldn't provide an Aadhaar card, as per the ministry's requirements. Her biometrics, too, are locked at the moment.

In another case, Tanmay Saha, a resident of Silchar, Assam who is currently working in a public sector bank, fears that he will be stuck there for years as he cannot apply in any private sector firm without an Aadhaar card. Saha is the only one in his family whose biometrics are locked at the moment, as the rest of his family members made it to the draft NRC list in 2018. "Not just with jobs, but a lot of people in Assam find their overall lives to have reached a stand-still. Students cannot apply for scholarships, young people cannot maintain EPF accounts and senior citizens cannot receive pensions, as all of it requires Aadhaar"

We request you to please look into this topic and please make a video on this topic so that we can come out of this problem as I am from those 27 lakhs people who has been facing this issue since 5 years as we are not being provided with Aadhar card and for this reason we are unable to apply for any jobs ,avail scholarships, ration cards, as well as not being able to apply for driving license and the  list  goes on.

Please have a look on this topic and please speak on this problem as it will be a help for 27 lakhs people in Assam and we would be forever grateful for you. As the governement has been ignoring the problem from the last five years. 

We believe that your words can bring change to the entire nation and we really want us to help in this problem

Warm Regards,
27 lakhs people from Assam.

Aaj main yahan likh hoon, aap sabhi ke samaksh, desh ki bhavishya ki disha mein ek zaroori charcha karne ke liye. Hum sabhi jaante hain ki hamara desh, ek anmol ratna hai, jise hamare purvajon ne bahut mahnet se banaya hai. Lekin aaj ke samay mein, humare desh mein kuch asurakshit sthitiyan hain, jo hamare vikas ko rok rahe hain.

Sabse pehle, humein apni rajnaitik vyavastha par vichar karna chahiye. Hum sabko yah swikar karna hoga ki bhrashtachar hamare desh ke liye ek badi samasya hai. Pradhanmantri ki party ko bhrasht netaon ko apni party mein shamil karne ki anumati dena ya unhein koi jagah dena, yah galat hai. Humein desh ki seva ke liye sachhe aur imandar netaon ko protsahan dena chahiye, na ki bhrashtachar ko badhava dena.

Dusri baat, mehangai par charcha karna zaroori hai. Mehangai ek aam aadmi ke liye badi samasya hai. Hamari sarkar ko mehangai ke prati samvedansheel hona chahiye aur janta ke hit mein kadam uthane chahiye, n ki mehangai ko bhulakar anya mudde par dhyan dena chahiye.

Teesri baat, humein sakahari logo ka samarthan karna chahiye. Aajkal ki lifestyle mein, sakahari bhojan ka mahatva bahut badh gaya hai. Hum sabhi ko isse jude logo ko protsahit karna chahiye, unki samasyaon ka samadhan karne mein sahayak banne ki disha mein kadam uthana chahiye.

Lekin yeh na bhulein ki hamare desh mein bahut se log hain jo mansahari hain. Unka bhi samman karna hamara kartavya hai. Hum unke hiton ka vichar karte hue unki samasyaon ka samadhan karna chahiye.

Chauthi baat, desh ke netaon ko sashakt karna aur unki jimmedariyon ko thik se nibhana hamara farz hai. Chunav se pehle, humein un netaon ki gunvatta ko pehchan kar unhein chunav ladne ki anumati deni chahiye. Anya rajnaitik dalon ke netaon ko jail mein dalna aur unke khate freeze karna, desh ke hit mein zaroori kadam ho sakte hain.

Ant mein, ek neta dwara desh ke sanvidhan ko badalne ki koi bhi koshish sakaratmak nahi hai. Hum sabhi ko sanvidhan ke mool tatvon ka samman karna chahiye aur unhein sudhar karne ki koi bhi prakriya mein bhaag lene se rokna chahiye.

Mujhe vishwas hai ki agar hum sab milkar sahi disha mein kadam uthayein, to hum hamare desh ko ek uchch sthiti tak pahuncha sakte hain.
